Here's a little secret about getting wax off a car
from a guy who used to own a detail shop - dissolve a
box of baking soda in 2 gallons of water, and wash the
car with it. It will strip all the wax off, usually in
one washing. Cost: about a buck and half. 

-John Cloonan


